ny Award for Best Musical|Tony Award]]-winning [[musical theatre|musical]] ''[[In the Heights]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/143122-26-Miles-Quiara-Hudes-Mother-Daughter-Road-Trip-Tale-Gets-Chicago-Premiere-Starting-Oct-16 |title=26 Miles, Quiara Hudes' Mother-Daughter Road-Trip Tale, Gets Chicago Premiere Starting Oct. 16 |publisher=Playbill.com |date=17 September 2010 |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100921071804/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/143122-26-Miles-Quiara-Hudes-Mother-Daughter-Road-Trip-Tale-Gets-Chicago-Premiere-Starting-Oct-16 |archivedate=21 September 2010 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 de Jes\u00fas Esteves]]''', poet, lawyer, and judge<ref>{{cite book|title=Biograf\u00edas puertorrique\u00f1as: perfil hist\u00f3rico de un pueblo|year=1970|publisher=Troutman Press|author=Ces\u00e1reo Rosa-Nieves, Esther Mel\u00f3n de D\u00edaz|page=145}}</ref>\n* '''[[Zo\u00e9 Jim\u00e9nez Corretjer]]''', poet, author<ref>L\u00f3pez Baralt, Mercedes. ''Literatura Puertorrique\u00f1a del Siglo XX: Antolog\u00eda.'' San Juan: EDUPR, 2004.</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==L==\n{{div col}}\n* '''[[Lawrence La Fountain-Stokes]]''', writer<br /> ''Author of \"U\u00f1as pintadas de azul/Blue Fingernails\"''.<ref name=identity>Morales-D\u00edaz, Enrique. \"Identity of the 'Diasporican' Homosexual in the Literary Periphery.\" In Jos\u00e9 L. Torres-Padilla and Carmen Hayd\u00e9e Rivera, eds. ''Writing Off the Hyphen: New Perspectives on the Literature of the Puerto Rican Diaspora.'' Seattle: University of Washington Press, 2008. 295\u2013312. {{ISBN|978-0-295-98824-5}}</ref>\n* '''[[Enrique A. Laguerre]]''', writer<br />'' Laguerre was nominated for Nobel Prize in literature''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prpop.org/biografias/e_bios/enrique_laguerre.shtml |title= Enrique A. Laguerre|publisher=Prpop.org |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Eduardo Lalo]]''' (born 1960), writer<br />''