as]]''', author of the best-seller ''[[Down These Mean Streets]]''.<ref name=\"Thomas\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cheverote.com/bio.html |title=Piri Thomas' Life and Flows |publisher=Cheverote.com |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321022258/http://www.cheverote.com/bio.html |archivedate=21 March 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* '''[[Edwin Torres (Poet)|Edwin Torres]]''', \"[[Nuyorican Movement]]\" poet<ref name=\"aloud\">''Aloud: Voices from the Nuyorican Poets Cafe'' Holt. {{ISBN|0-8050-3257-6}}.</ref>\n* '''Judge [[Edwin Torres (Judge)|Edwin Torres]]''', writer<br />'' New York Supreme Court Justice who wrote'' [[Carlito's Way]].<ref name=\"herald\">{{cite news|url=http://www.puertorico-herald.org/issues/vol4n48/ProfTorres-en.html |title=Puerto Rico Profile: Judge Edwin Torres |date=1 December 2000 |publisher=Puerto Rico Herald |accessdate=2 November 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080106172450/http://www.puertorico-herald.org/issues/vol4n48/ProfTorres-en.html |archivedate=6 January 2008 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Justin Torres]]''' (born 1980), writer<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/25/books/review/we-the-animals-by-justin-torres-book-review.html | work=The New York Times | first=Joseph | last=Salvatore | title=We the Animals \u2014 By Justin Torres \u2014 Book Review | date=2011-09-23}}</ref>\n* '''[[Diego de Torres Vargas]]''' a [[priest]]<br> was the first person to write a book about the history of Puerto Rico.<ref name=\"HIPR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prfrogui.com/geocities/hommujerilustres.htm |title=Puertorrique\u00f1os Ilustres |accessdate=17 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080816022702/http://www.prfrogui.com/geocities/hommujerilustres.htm |archivedate=16 August 2008 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Luz Mar\u00eda Umpierre]]''', poet, scholar<ref>{{cite web|last=Rivera |first=Carmen Hayd\u00e9e |url=http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/pdf/377/37720102.pdf |title=Language is our only homelan': An Interview with Luz Mar\u00eda Umpierre |work=CENTRO - Journal of the Center for Puerto Rican Studies |volume=20.1 (Spring 2008) 13\u201321 |publisher=Redalyc.uaemex.mx |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406175256/http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/pdf/377/37720102.pdf |archivedate=6 April 2012 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Charlie V\u00e1zquez]]''', novelist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigfib.com/lit/vazquez.html |title=Author Profile Charlie Vazquez |publisher=Bigfib.com |date=14 July 2008 |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510162032/http://www.bigfib.com/lit/vazquez.html |archivedate=10 May 2012 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Lourdes V\u00e1zquez]]''', poet, short story writer, novelist<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=25745872|title=Un punto de vista diferente: entrevista a Lourdes V\u00e1zquez|first1=Selfa A.|last1=Chew|first2=Lourdes|last2=V\u00e1zquez|date=1 January 2004|journal=Bilingual Review / La Revista Biling\u00fce|volume=28|issue=3|pages=265\u2013268}}</ref>\n* '''[[Robert Vazquez-Pacheco]]''', author<ref name=identity/>\n* '''[[Ana Lydia Vega]]''', short story author, essayist<ref>Puleo, Augustus. \"Ana Lydia Vega, the Caribbean Storyteller.\" ''Afro-Hispanic Review'' 15.2 (Fall 1996): 21-25.</ref>\n* '''[[Bernardo Vega (writer)|Bernardo Vega]]''', novelist, author of ''The Memoirs of Bernardo Vega'' (1977, English ed. 1984)<ref name=Zimmerman/>\n* '''[[Edgardo Vega Yunqu\u00e9]]''' or '''Ed Vega''', novelist<ref name=Vega>{{cite news|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|last=Weber|first=Bruce|date=9 September 2008|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/09/books/09vegayunque.html|title=Edgardo Vega Yunqu\u00e9, Novelist of the Puerto Rican Experience in New York, Dies at 72.}}</ref> \n* '''[[Irene Vilar]]''', author and literary agent<br />''Vilar is the granddaughter of independence activist [[Lolita Lebr\u00f3n]]''.<ref>{{cite news |first=Robin |last=Abcarian |